f deceased persons to the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) to transport them to the mortuary. “We appeal to members of the public to comply with the COVID-19, lockdown and social distancing guidelines to avoid endangering themselves,” Oke-Osanyintolu said. He also urged the rescue workers to follow the social distancing guidelines of the Lagos state government. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. ...Survivor in critical condition By Olasunkanmi Akoni Tragedy occurred on Tuesday in Lagos when a Dangote Cement silo truck with unknown registration number, while on top speed suddenly, fell on a commercial car, OPEL brand, along Epe-Expressway, crushing six of the seven occupants to death on the spot. The victims… April 1, 2020 In "Metro" .Survivor in critical condition By Olasunkanmi Akoni Tragedy occurred on Tuesday in Lagos when a Dangote Cement silo truck with unknown registration number, while on top speed suddenly, fell on a commercial car, OPEL brand, along Epe-Expressway, crushing six of the seven occupants to death on the spot. The victims… April 1, 2020 In "News" By Olasunkanmi Akoni It was a lucky day for three motorists when they narrowly escaped death, Tuesday, following a crash involving their vehicles at Lekki-Ibeju, along Epe Expressway, Lagos. The accident, according to an eyewitness, occurred at about 4pm. The crash involved a Sport Utility Vehicle, SUV,  Highlander, with an unknown… October 30, 2019 In "News"